  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Taskade is an AI-powered productivity and project management platform founded in 2017 by John Xie, Dionis Loire, and Stan Chang. The company went through Y Combinator's Summer 2019 batch and is headquartered in San Francisco, California, operating as a remote-first team; it has raised seed funding including from Grishin Robotics and Y Combinator. Taskade unifies task lists, collaborative documents, mind maps, kanban boards, and calendars into a single flexible workspace, and has increasingly focused on AI features that let users build and deploy custom AI agents and automated workflows alongside their projects. It is aimed at freelancers, startups, remote teams, and businesses that want an all-in-one workspace rather than juggling separate tools for notes, tasks, and chat. Key features include AI-generated project templates and outlines, multiplayer real-time editing, customizable AI agents for tasks like research or customer support, workflow automations, and 100+ integrations on paid tiers. Pricing is freemium: the Free plan includes limited AI apps, agents, and automations with 250 MB of storage, while paid plans (Pro at $10 per month, Business at $25 per month, Max at $100 per month, and Enterprise at $250 per month, all billed annually) scale up monthly AI credit allowances, storage, integrations, and advanced administrative controls like SSO and role-based access.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '83e84bc7-624a-4103-b7df-a6cdfba35f21';

